Solution:

ğŸ§© Problem Statement

Given an integer array nums of size n, partition it into two subsets such that the absolute difference between the sums of the two subsets is minimized.

Return the minimum possible absolute difference.

ğŸ” Explanation

You need to divide the array into two subsets S1 and S2 such that:

|sum(S1) - sum(S2)| is minimum


Each element must belong to exactly one of the two subsets.

ğŸ“ Constraints

1 <= nums.length <= 100

0 <= nums[i] <= 1000

The sum of elements will not exceed 10^5

ğŸ’¡ Example 1
Input
nums = [1, 2, 3, 9]

Output
3

Explanation

Possible partitions:

{1, 2, 3} and {9}

Sum1 = 6

Sum2 = 9

Difference = |6 - 9| = 3

This is the minimum possible difference.

ğŸ’¡ Example 2
Input
nums = [1, 2, 7]

Output
4

Explanation

Possible partitions:

{1, 2} and {7}

Sum1 = 3

Sum2 = 7

Difference = 4

ğŸ’¡ Example 3
Input
nums = [1, 6, 11, 5]

Output
1

Explanation

{1, 6, 5} â†’ Sum = 12

{11} â†’ Sum = 11

Difference = 1

This is the minimum achievable difference.

import java.util.*;

class Main {
    
    public static boolean canForm(int[] nums,int target,int idx) {
        if(target==0) return true;

        if(idx==0) {
            if(nums[idx]==target) return true;
            else return false;
        }

        boolean not_choose = canForm(nums,target,idx-1);
        boolean choose = false;
        if(nums[idx]<=target) {
            choose= canForm(nums,target-nums[idx],idx-1);
        }

        return choose || not_choose;
    }

    public static int minimumSubsetSumDiff(int[] nums) {

        int total = 0;
        for(int num: nums) total+=num;

        boolean[] dp = new boolean[total+1];
        dp[0] = true;

        for(int target=1;target<=total;target++) {
            dp[target] = canForm(nums,target,nums.length-1);
        }

        int min_diff = Integer.MAX_VALUE;
        for(int i=0;i<=total;i++) {
            int s = (dp[i] ? i : 0);
            int abs = Math.abs(2*s - total);
            min_diff = Math.min(min_diff,abs);
        }

        return min_diff;
    }

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Scanner sc = new Scanner(System.in);
        int n = sc.nextInt();
        int[] val = new int[n];
        for(int i=0;i<n;i++) {
            val[i] = sc.nextInt();
        }

        System.out.println(minimumSubsetSumDiff(val));
    }
}
